{% endif %}
{% if choices %}
The passage ends where these choices can naturally follow: {{ choices | join(" / ") }}.
{% else %}
This is an ending: land it completely.
{% endif %}

You are not expected to add a micro_detail — most passages add none. Add AT
MOST ONE, and only if this scene genuinely surfaced something a later writer
would need: a new universal fact about an entity (true on every playthrough,
never path-dependent), or a sharper version of one already listed above (reuse
its key — that is an UPDATE, not a duplicate). Never contradict an established
fact; never restate one just to fill the slot. A detail is a NOTE for later
writers, not prose: at most 12 words, in note form ("stance: wide,
fencer-like"), never a sentence copied from your passage. Its shape is
{"entity": an entity id from the cast above, "key": a fact name, "value": the
fact}. If nothing genuinely new surfaced, add nothing.
